  "finding": "The best out-of-fold charge closure is extra_trees_with_rate with res68 0.00882 [0.00733, 0.01097], versus the frozen traditional stratified closure at 0.04677. The explicit rate-support gate abstains on 14.83% of rows and gives conformal coverage 0.894; low-support cells concentrate in high-saturation, high-tail, sparse-topology atoms. Rate residual features improve the best HGB/ExtraTrees closures only modestly relative to waveform/topology features, so the operational recommendation is to use the support veto as a downstream P04/S14 guardrail rather than treat A/B rate as an energy correction.",
  "git_commit": "124659c50f1b88bd01cad4b91e2ab9672b7ea27e",
  "runtime_sec": 530.4
